messages.message:
Heads up, if you ever get this error message:
```429 Too Many Requests - Server message: toomanyrequests: You have reached your pull rate limit. You may increase the limit by authenticating and upgrading: https://www.docker.com/increase-rate-limit```
Please double check your `~/.docker/config` file, it should have this:
```owner@dev:~$ cat ~/.docker/config
{
  "credHelpers": {
     "gcr.io": "gcloud",
     "549230430157.dkr.ecr.us-east-2.amazonaws.com": "ecr-login",
     "601729033846.dkr.ecr.us-east-2.amazonaws.com": "ecr-login"
  }
}```
For some reason, my sandbox didn't have that file (despite it being synced relatively recently).
